Soweto doctors say they are living in fear. There has been a spate of attacks on surgeries - with at least one every week for the past ten weeks. eNCA's Barry Bateman is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some Soweto doctors say they are living in fear following a spate of attacks on surgeries. Last month Dr. George Koboka was gunned down inside his surgery. Koboka was murdered at the practice where he fought to preserve and improve life. READ: SA Health Emergency | Another doctor attacked on duty The Soweto Independent Practitioners Association has called on authorities to act - as some members are considering moving out of their township. Community leaders have vowed to march to the Diepkloof police station soon. eNCA’s Barry Bateman shares more details in the video above.